Persian Gulf Stocks: Abu Dhabi Commercial Bank and Tamweel

-- B y   Z a h r a   H a n k i r
-- 
2011-06-15T10:54:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-15/persian-gulf-stocks-abu-dhabi-commercial-bank-and-tamweel.html
Dubai’s DFM General Index rallied
2.2 percent, the biggest gain among world equity indexes. Abu
Dhabi’s  ADX General Index (ADSMI)  jumped 1.2 percent to the highest
since January.  The following stocks rose or fell in the Persian Gulf
region. Symbols are in parentheses.        Abu Dhabi Commercial Bank PJSC (ADCB)   rose to the
highest since October 2008, advancing 1.9 percent to 3.16
dirhams. The Malaysian government said the bank will sign an
agreement to sell its stake in Kuala Lumpur-based lender RHB
Capital Bhd. to Aabar Investments PJSC on June 17.        Tamweel PJSC (TAMWEEL)   climbed the most in two weeks,
gaining 2.5 percent to 97.4 fils. The shares of the home-
financing company majority owned by Dubai Islamic Bank PJSC will
be included in the  DFM General Index (DFMGI)  and the banking sub-index
from July 3.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zahra Hankir in Dubai at 
 zhankir@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
